Connect String

Almost all Sqoop commands use a "--connect" string to connect to a database. 
This string inorder to connect to the database needs the following information:

  -> Database type (mysql, Oracle etc)
  -> Hostname
  -> Portnumber
  -> Database Name 
  
  The syntax is as follows:
  sqoop <command> \
    --connect jdbc:<database type>:<Hostname>:<port number>/<database name> \
    --username <userid>
    --password <password>
